{"word":"σκορπιοειδής","slug":"σκορπιοειδής","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n95162\" key=\"skorpioeidh/s\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"suff\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">σκορπιο-ειδής</orth>, <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">ές</itype>, <sense id=\"n95162.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">scorpion-like</tr_>, only in form <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">σκορπιώδης</foreign> (q.v.). </sense> <sense n=\"II\" id=\"n95162.1\" level=\"2\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">σκορπιοειδές, <gen lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gen\">τό</gen></foreign>, <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">scorpion-wort</tr_> <pb n=\"1615\" TEIform=\"pb\"/> (so called because of the <abbr TEIform=\"abbr\">like</abbr> ness of its seed to a scorpion's tail), <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">Scorpiurus sulcata</tr_>, <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Dsc.\">Dsc.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">4.192</biblScope> </bibl>; cf. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">σκορπίουρος</foreign>.</sense> </entryFree>"}]}